    "domain": "Standard English Conventions",
    "type": "Form, Structure, and Sense",
    "difficulty": "hard",
    "passage": "Among the most surprising findings of the decade-long study of cephalopod cognition ______ the discovery that octopuses can recognize individual human faces, a capacity once thought unique to vertebrates with far larger brains.",
